.TH MOONPI-SAFE 1 "2026" "MoonPi" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
moonpi-safe \- clean shutdown wrapper for Moonlight streaming sessions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B moonpi-safe
.I host-ip
.RI [ moonlight-args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B moonpi-safe
is a thin wrapper around
.BR moonlight-stream (1)
that ensures the remote session is cleanly terminated when the stream exits,
whether by the user pressing the quit hotkey, an error, or a signal.
.PP
It is normally invoked automatically by
.BR moonpi (1)
and not called directly by the user.
.SH BEHAVIOUR
.TP
1.
A SIGINT/SIGTERM trap is installed. If the process receives either signal
(e.g. from Ctrl-C or systemd stop), it sends
.B moonlight quit
to the host before exiting.
.TP
2.
.B moonlight stream
is started with the supplied arguments. The process is not
.BR exec (3)\'d
so the trap remains active for the lifetime of the stream.
.TP
3.
When the stream exits cleanly (e.g. user pressed Shift-Ctrl-Alt-Q inside
Moonlight),
.B moonpi-safe
sends
.B moonlight quit
to the host and exits with the same return code as
.BR moonlight-stream .
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of
.B moonlight stream
unless a signal was caught, in which case it exits 0.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR moonpi (1),
.BR moonlight (1)
